## Env Schema Add

When you change any of the matched files:

1. **Read** `agent-os/skills/env-schema-add/SKILL.md`.
2. **Place** the new key under the correct top-level half (`# GitHub Secrets`
   or `# GitHub Variables`) and sub-section in `.env.example`. Section IS
   classification — `pnpm github:sync` pushes by section, no separate classifier.
3. **Run** `pnpm tool:sync-env-example` to verify schema ↔ template parity and
   get the PR description snippet.
4. **Update** local `.env.<environment>` files manually without discarding real
   values, then `pnpm github:sync <environment> --dry-run` for each hosted environment to
   confirm the new key lands under the right `[secret]` / `[variable]` column.
5. **Add** the "Environment variable changes" block printed by the sync tool
   to the PR description.

See **`docs/deployment/runbooks/add-new-environment.md`** for the full hosted-environment workflow.
